# Given a dataframe returns the column indicated by 'select', applying
# filter 'filterCondition'. For any column which is not 'Time' it also applies 
# Moving average
def getDFWithFilter(df, filterColumn, filterCondition, select, minTime = None):
    if minTime is None:
        df = df[df[filterColumn] == filterCondition ][select] 
    else:
        df = df[df['Time'] >= minTime]
        df=  df[df[filterColumn] == filterCondition ][select]
    if select != "Time":
        df = df.cumsum()
        df /= (np.arange(len(df)) +1)
        #df = df.rolling(8, min_periods=1).sum()/8
    return df

#   INDUSTRIAL PRODUCTION MoM 

fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()

ax1.plot(priceAndEc['Time'], priceAndEc['Price'].rolling(window=5).mean(), color='b', linewidth=0.3)

ax1.set_xlabel('Date')
# Make the y-axis label, ticks and tick labels match the line color.
ax1.set_ylabel('EURUSD', color='b', fontsize = 30)

ax2 = ax1.twinx()

ax2.plot(getDFWithFilter(priceAndEc, 'What', IT_IND_PROD_MOM, 'Time'),
         getDFWithFilter(priceAndEc, 'What', IT_IND_PROD_MOM, 'Actual'), 'r-', label = IT_IND_PROD_MOM)
ax2.set_ylabel(IT_IND_PROD_MOM, color='r')

ax2.plot(getDFWithFilter(priceAndEc, 'What', FR_IND_PROD_MOM, 'Time'),
         getDFWithFilter(priceAndEc, 'What', FR_IND_PROD_MOM, 'Actual'), 'lightseagreen', label = FR_IND_PROD_MOM)


ax2.plot(getDFWithFilter(priceAndEc, 'What', GE_IND_PROD_MOM, 'Time'),
         getDFWithFilter(priceAndEc, 'What', GE_IND_PROD_MOM, 'Actual'), 'green', label = GE_IND_PROD_MOM)



ax2.set_ylabel("Industrial Production (MoM)", color = 'black', fontsize = 30)

fig.tight_layout()
fig.legend(loc="upper left", prop={'size': 16})

plt.show()

Italy and France did not recover yet from the recent crisis, average MoM since 2016 is indeed below 0%, Germany has recovered in 2012 and now growing around 0.1 month on month.¶
